,Recommended,251830,11062588,"Posted: 3 July, 2014",all,SetTheCat,"I absolutely love this game. The grimy, corrupt city feels like a 1970s caricature of New York, with all the necessary absurdities including disco, organized crime and sewer gators. A flat world of paper and stickers is vindicated by colorful themes, creative implementation and a great soundtrack, things I often feel the AAA titles are lacking. Emphasis on mind reading, psychology and the mind itself feel reminiscent of Psychonauts by Double Fine.If anything, my only complaint would be play time. With only two hours played I appear to already be close to 1/3 of the way to the end. Despite this, 6 hours of stimulation that far exceeds the enjoyment of any movie I've seen in theaters this year makes the $15 investment well worth the cost."
