,Recommended,251830,20241043,"Posted: 2 January, 2016",all,TheDContinuum,"This was a fun game, and a great concept. Your character is able to read people's minds thanks to an alien creature inside his head. The art is fantastic, with everything (including the characters) made out of cardboard or paper like a diorama. You can even see the bits of corrugation in the cardboard from the side! You can use your mental powers to find stickers all over the world that you can use to accomplish different tasks. For example, you can read someone's thoughts so they start thinking about something, which appears as a sticker in a thought balloon, which you can now place on them to put them to sleep! It's kind of like a 2.5-D puzzle-platformer (more like 2.75-D, since you can occasionally move in the third dimension), but with true 3D depth in the scenery. Attention to detail is amazing. My only problem is that the game is too short (it took me about 4 hours, including lots of wandering around trying to find things that I had overlooked)."
,Recommended,251830,19865413,"Posted: 23 December, 2015",all,TheAmazingBunzai,"This game is great. The art style and soundtrack are immediately appealing. The story is humorous, weird, and actually pretty dark at times; but it tells it's story without ever taking itself too seriously.The gameplay itself is also fun and interesting. It's mostly split into two catergories: stealth/eluding segments and exploration puzzle solving segments. The stealth segments are fun, with you grappling around with your sticky mind hand to elude guards. The exploration is my favorite part though. It's extremely satisfying going around solving people's problems in order to help yourself get further. There's nver a dull moment, and characters always have something interesting to say.I'd recommend this game. In terms of length, it's pretty short. So if you want to play this game, but feel like 5 hours of game isn't worth the price, wait till it goes on sale. You won't regret it."
