76561198051743158,Recommended,251830,28247164,"Posted: 7 December, 2016",all,jslotkin,"Pro tip: Try TURNING OFF SUBTITLES to make the game funnier! I don't know if it is just me, but I really wish someone had told me this before I got so far into the game.This game is not very long (took 6 hours of playtime to complete), very challenging, or (I suspect) very replayable. Play it for the amazing visual style and the humor. The writing is not as consistently excellent as the visual presentation. But, at least in my experience, the writing feels a lot less stiff and more amusingly quirky without subtitles.I started out with subtitles on and was having a hard time getting into the game. Then I turned them off by accident and suddenly found myself enjoying the game significantly more.One thing I wish the game had was more flexibility in applying stickers. As far as I can tell, each sticker has one right usage, and when you try the wrong sticker, nothing happens. It would be much more interesting if there were multiple viable ways to use stickers, or if they at least had some amusing things happen when using the wrong sticker."
