,Recommended,251830,26500521,"Posted: 9 November, 2016",all,IVI00101,Fun platformer/quest.
,Recommended,251830,28727765,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,Dreadjaws,"Stick It To The Man is a hilarious adventure game first, but it also contains elements of platforming and stealth, and it's what I imagine what would look like if Beetlejuice-era Tim Burton made a stage play.  You play as Ray, a regular man with a regular life who by accident is suddenly merged with an alien entity named Ted, who confers him telepathy and telekinesis via a giant purple hand that sticks out of his head.  On the run from a shady organization with evil plans, Ray must find a way to return to normal while also stopping the organization, all the while using his newfound powers to help people around him.I've been interested in this game since its release, but I've put off its purchase for a long time.  I instantly regretted that once I started playing.  This game is easily worth its full price.  Following the storyline and getting every achievement will net you between 4 to 5 hours of playtime, which is the perfect spot for the price while still mantaining the novelty of the gameplay.It's a really easy game (though, like in all adventure games, you're bound to get stuck for a bit at least once), it's more about the experience than the challenge.  Outlandish characters, fourth-wall breaking, and overall funny dialogue are the meat of the game.  Gameplay-wise, the majority consists of using your abilities to solve puzzles, by both reading minds and make use of stickers to change around the environment.  There's also some light platforming and a few stealth sections, but they're there just to add some variety and they're mostly a means to an end.  They're not by any means bad, they're just the least interesting part of the experience.What else can I say?  Buy this game now, you won't regret it."
